(44, 12, 7, 33, 7, 9, 9, 'light shined in the prison', 'Light and Deliverance Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine intervention and deliverance from darkness. In Acts, the angel brings light to Peter in prison, while Micah speaks of being brought forth to the light after bearing indignation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 12, 9, 19, 126, 1, 1, 'thought he saw a vision', 'Dreams and Reality in Deliverance', 'This connection highlights the theme of deliverance from captivity and the dreamlike quality of miraculous events. Both passages emphasize a sense of disbelief and wonder in the face of divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 12, 9, 58, 11, 8, 8, NULL, 'Faith and Uncertainty in Action', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of going out in faith without full understanding. Peter follows the angel, unsure if it is real, while Abraham obeys God''s call, not knowing his destination.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 12, 9, 1, 45, 26, 26, 'wist not that it was true', 'Unbelief in Divine Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of disbelief in divine messages. In both passages, characters experience doubt regarding extraordinary revelations, with Peter thinking he saw a vision and Jacob fainting from disbelief.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
