(44, 12, 9, 44, 26, 19, 19, 'wist not that it was true', 'Connection of Vision and Obedience', 'This connection highlights the theme of vision in both passages. In Acts 12:9, the angelic intervention is perceived as a vision, while in Acts 26:19, obedience to a heavenly vision is emphasized.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 12, 9, 47, 12, 1, 3, 'wist not that it was true', 'Visions and Revelations Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the experience of visions, with Acts describing Peter''s uncertainty about his angelic encounter and 2 Corinthians discussing a man''s experience of being caught up to the third heaven. This connection highlights the theme of divine revelation and the ambiguity surrounding such experiences.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
