(44, 12, 10, 23, 45, 1, 2, 'the iron gate that leadeth unto the city', 'Divine Gate Opening', 'Both passages emphasize the opening of gates as a sign of divine intervention. In Acts, the iron gate opens of its own accord, while in Isaiah, the Lord promises to open gates before Cyrus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 12, 10, 1, 40, 3, 3, NULL, 'Prison and Deliverance Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being in ward or prison and the subsequent deliverance from it. In Acts, Peter is freed from prison by an angel, while in Genesis, Joseph is confined in a similar setting.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
