(44, 12, 11, 27, 6, 22, 22, 'the Lord hath sent his angel', 'Divine Deliverance Through Angels', 'Both passages emphasize divine intervention through angels in moments of peril. Peter acknowledges his deliverance from Herod, while Daniel credits an angel for protecting him from lions.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 12, 11, 27, 3, 28, 28, 'hath sent his angel', 'Divine Deliverance Through Angels', 'Both passages emphasize the role of an angel sent by God to deliver His faithful servants from peril. This connection highlights the theme of divine intervention in times of distress.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 12, 11, 61, 2, 9, 9, 'the Lord hath sent his angel, and hath delivered me', 'Divine Deliverance Theme', 'Both passages emphasize God''s ability to deliver His people from danger. In Acts, Peter acknowledges his deliverance from Herod, while in 2 Peter, it is stated that the Lord knows how to deliver the godly from temptations.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 12, 11, 19, 34, 7, 7, 'delivered me out of the hand of Herod', 'Divine Deliverance by Angels', 'Both passages emphasize the role of angels in delivering those who fear the Lord. Peter''s realization of deliverance aligns with the assurance that the angel of the Lord protects and rescues believers.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 12, 11, 19, 33, 18, 18, 'the Lord hath sent his angel', 'Divine Deliverance and Hope', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine intervention and protection. Both passages emphasize the Lord''s watchfulness over those who trust in Him, as seen in Peter''s deliverance and the assurance of God''s eye upon those who hope in His mercy.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
