(44, 12, 15, 1, 48, 16, 16, 'It is his angel', 'Connection of Angels in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the role of angels in biblical narratives. In Acts, the mention of ''his angel'' suggests a protective or redemptive function similar to the ''Angel which redeemed me'' in Genesis.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 12, 15, 18, 9, 16, 16, 'Thou art mad', 'Perception of Divine Communication', 'This connection highlights the theme of doubt in recognizing divine communication. In Acts, the believers doubt the reality of Peter''s angel, while in Job, the speaker expresses skepticism about being heard by God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 12, 17, 44, 21, 40, 40, NULL, 'Silence and Beckoning Motif', 'This connection highlights the act of beckoning with the hand to establish silence before speaking. Both passages emphasize the importance of communication in moments of significance.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
